    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-03T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-03T03:00:00-05:00" n="668"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.61A/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="7" xml:id="d668fn7">Also accredited as Minister to Saudi
                        Arabia.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-03T10:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 3, 1942—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>190. My 2049, December 30, 11 a.m., and my 189, February 3, 9 a.m.<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d668fn8">Neither printed.</note> Has the Department any information
                    as to the appointment of an agricultural expert to Saudi Arabia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
